Notes:

Very old -> 500BCE

In India, religion focused on the Vedras (Hinduism)

Siddhartha Gautama, a prince, leaves the palace on a spiritual journey.

His encounter with human suffering and his response to it lead to his formulation of a way of life which is neither too accentual or hedonistic.

The middle way

The eightfold path is a response to:

The 4 noble truths.

Enlightenment is the product of following the eight fold path.

The eight fold pathway to over several lifetimes (reincarnation).

Nirvana - after a physical life, ends a mystery

Bodhisattva - people who are close to nirvana - teach others the way

Arhat - people who have achieved nirvana - but still in a physical state.

Buddhism has spread across the world - namely Asia.

Dali lama - Tibetan Buddhist leader

Reincarnated Buddhism.
